Celtic winger Aleksandar Tonev has been charged with racially abusing Aberdeen defender Shay Logan. Celtic: Aleksandar Tonev charged over alleged racism  Celtic winger Aleksandar Tonev has been charged with racially abusing Aberdeen defender Shay Logan.  
 The 24-year-old Bulgarian, who is on loan from Aston Villa, has been called to a Scottish FA hearing on 9 October. 
 Tonev must answer a charge of &quot;excessive misconduct by the use of offensive, insulting and abusive language of a racist nature&quot;. 
 The midfielder has until 26 September to respond to the governing body's notice of complaint. 
 Tonev and Logan were direct opponents for much of Saturday's match, which  Celtic won 2-1. 
 